<div class="definition" id="definition-EELT" acro="EELT" titletext="Eigenvalue and Eigenvector of a Linear Transformation">
<h5 class="definition">
<span class="type">Definition </span><span class="acro">EELT</span> <span class="titletext"> Eigenvalue and Eigenvector of a Linear Transformation</span>
</h5>
<p>Suppose that $\ltdefn{T}{V}{V}$ is a linear transformation.  Then a nonzero vector $\vect{v}\in V$ is an <em class="term">eigenvector</em> of $T$ for the <em class="term">eigenvalue</em> $\lambda$ if $\lt{T}{\vect{v}}=\lambda\vect{v}$.</p>
